                            <comment id="14438303" author="dennisl@apache.org" created="Tue, 6 Aug 2013 03:48:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Michael,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I seem to recall that some plugin (can&apos;t remember which one though) uses relative references to be able to validate the files when in offline mode. I don&apos;t know if this applies to the JXR plugin or not. Could you try running all tests in offline mode to see if they all still pass, just to make sure?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438313" author="michael-o" created="Tue, 6 Aug 2013 13:58:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dennis, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;D:\Projekte\jxr-trunk&amp;gt;mvn --offline clean install integration-test site -Prun-its,reporting &amp;gt; jxr-offline.log
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Output is attached.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Though I would recommend to set Javadoc plugin to quiet mode. It is very chatty.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438153" author="dennisl@apache.org" created="Tue, 6 Aug 2013 14:19:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Michael, that looks good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438246" author="rfscholte" created="Tue, 6 Aug 2013 14:28:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=michael-o&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;michael-o&quot;&gt;michael-o&lt;/a&gt;, please always use &lt;tt&gt;verify&lt;/tt&gt; instead in &lt;tt&gt;integration-test&lt;/tt&gt;, since only during this phase the results are checked. In other words: in an IT had failed, it won&apos;t break the build yet. That&apos;ll happen during the &lt;tt&gt;verify&lt;/tt&gt; phase. (And verify is much easier to type &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; )&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438337" author="michael-o" created="Tue, 6 Aug 2013 14:34:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Robert, thanks. I will re-run the tests and upload an updated log file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
